<p style="margin: 0; color: #555555; font-size: 15px; font-family: Helvetica,sans-serif;">Hello {{lead.First Name:default=there}},<br /><br />We invite you to read&nbsp;<a style="color: #059a91; text-decoration: none;" href="https://pivotal.io/gartner-market-guide-for-application-platforms">Gartner&rsquo;s Market Guide for Application Platforms</a> to learn about the state of the Application            Platform-as-a-Service 
  (aPaaS) market, and explore key findings and recommendations.
              <br /><br /> To meet their digital business requirements, companies are looking for platforms that support continuous innovation, developer velocity, DevOps, and new architectural paradigms such as microservices and cloud-native architectures.
   One important finding of this Market Guide is that as Java EE and other three-tier frameworks, such as <a style="color: #88888; text-decoration: none;" href="ASP.NET"><span style="color: #5c5c5c;">ASP.NET</span></a>, fade in relevance, application leaders must build a strategy which includes alternative platforms that support cloud-native applications.
             <br /><br /> In this report, Gartner&rsquo;s Anne Thomas and Aashish Gupta provide an overview of application platform strategies and capabilities to help you choose the right one for your modernization initiatives.</p>
